   <head type='DD'>
      <!-- PREMIS Semantic unit 1.1.1 -->
      <gi>objectIdentifierType</gi>
   </head>

   <div type="fullName">
      <!-- PREMIS Semantic components -->
      <p xml:lang="en">objectIdentifierType</p>
   </div>

   <div type="definition">
      <!-- PREMIS Definition -->
      <p xml:lang="en">A designation of the domain within which the object identifier is unique.</p>
   </div>

   <div type="rationale">
      <!-- PREMIS Rationale -->
      <p xml:lang="en">Description you can use <gi>anglebrackets</gi></p>
      <p>Identifier values cannot be assumed to be unique across domains; the combination of
            <gi>objectIdentifierType</gi> and <gi>objectIdentifierValue</gi> should ensure
         uniqueness.</p>
   </div>

   <div type="usagenotes">
      <!-- PREMIS Usage notes -->
      <p xml:lang="en">The type of the identifier may be implicit within the repository as long as
         it can be explicitly communicated when the digital object is disseminated outside of it.
      </p>
   </div>

   <div type="datatype">
      <!-- PREMIS Data constraint URL below should be live after transformation -->
      <p>Value should be taken from a controlled vocabulary. A controlled vocabulary is available at <ref target="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/identifiers.html">http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/identifiers.html</ref>.</p>
   </div>
   
